summary: (3e)-3,7-dimethylocta-1,3,6-triene and nerolidol are both terpenes mentioned in the context of a sequence comparison of terpene synthases from various plant species. The context highlights the alignment of sequences related to different terpene synthases, including those that produce nerolidol. While they are part of the same biochemical pathway, the specific relationship or interaction between these two compounds is not elaborated upon in detail.
